n+n+1+n+2 & =-54 \\
3 n+3 & =-54 \\
3 n & =-57 \\
n & =-19 \quad 1^{\text {st }} \text { integer }
\end{aligned}$$

Step 5. Solve the equation.
Combine like terms.
Subtract three from each side.
$n+1 \quad 2^{\text {nd }}$ integer

Divide each side by three.
$$-19+1$$
-18
