\section*{EXAMPLE 2.30}

Solve the formula $S=2 \pi r^{2}+2 \pi r h$ for $h$.

\section*{(1) Solution}

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline Write the formula. & $S=2 \pi r^{2}+2 \pi r h$ \\
\hline Isolate the $h$ term by subtracting $2 \pi r^{2}$ from each side. & $S-2 \pi r^{2}=2 \pi r^{2}-2 \pi r^{2}+2 \pi r h$ \\
\hline Simplify. & $S-2 \pi r^{2}=2 \pi r h$ \\
\hline Solve for $h$ by dividing both sides by $2 \pi r$. & $\frac{S-2 \pi r^{2}}{2 \pi r}=\frac{2 \pi r h}{2 \pi r}$ \\
\hline Simplify. & $\frac{S-2 \pi r^{2}}{2 \pi r}=h$ \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
